      "writtenOn": "2020-01-29T18:00:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please phrase this in terms of what it is for (as opposed to what it does).\n\nExample:\n\n  /**\n   * Renders the given string in a XSS-safe way, with the following changes:\n   *   - Any HTML is escaped (\"\u003c\" and \"\u003e\" become \"\u0026lt;\", \"\u0026gt;\", etc.).\n   *   - Line breaks are replaced with \"\u003cbr/\u003e\".\n   *   - URLs are wrapped in anchor tags.\n   *   - Bug shorthand (e.g. \"skia:1324\") are wrapped in anchor tags.\n   *\n   * To be used in lit-html templates as in the example below:\n   * \n   *   html`user input: ${escapeAndLinkify(untrustedUserInput)}`;\n   */",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 11,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "5a47d01658ba0513db1092eabfca018ce717607c",
